> Last week Patrick, Luke and Ed headed out to the sticks to visit our esteemed butcher Nick 'The Knife'. He's actually a lot less scary than he sounds and he's been in the butchery business since he was knee-high to a grasshopper. Nick's big tip for this recipe is to put the steak in the freezer for 30 mins before you slice it and you'll be able to get paper thin slices really easily!

Boil a #pot{} of water for the noodles. Peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{2} and the @red chilli{1}(fine chopped, seeds removed if you like it less spicy). Grate a ¼ tsp of the @orange{1} zest and squeeze out its juice.

Hold the @ginger{1} in one hand and using the edge of a #spoon{} peel off the skin. Now finely chop the ginger. Finely slice the @spring onion{2}, separating the white parts from the green.

Slice the @flank steak{1} as thinly as your knife skills allow. Coat the strips in half of the @cornflour{2} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Heat 1 tsp of @olive oil{1%tsp} on high heat in a #non-stick frying pan{}. When the oil is really hot, stir fry the steak for ~{2%mins} and then keep it to the side.

Cook the @egg noodle nest{2} in the boiling water with ¼ tsp of @salt{¼%tsp} for around ~{4%mins}. The noodles are ready when they are 'al dente' (i.e. they still have a hint of firmness left in the middle). Drain the noodles and put them back in the pot with cold water for later.

Mix together the orange juice and @soy sauce{1.5} in a #small saucepan{}. Stir in the remaining cornflour, the orange zest and the @?sugar{1%tsp}.

> Tip: Make sure you mix it thoroughly so there are no lumps.

Put the pan on medium heat, bring to a simmer and cook for ~{2-3%mins} or until it has reduced down slightly.

Heat 2 tsp of @olive oil{2%tsp} in your now empty non-stick frying pan on high heat. Once hot, cook the garlic, ginger, white parts of the spring onion and 1 tsp of chopped chilli (less if you like it mild). After ~{1%minute} add in the @mangetout{1} and cook for ~{2%mins}.

Give your soy sauce mixture another good stir. Add your steak strips into the pan followed by the soy sauce mixture. Drain and add the noodles (don't worry that they're wet as this will add to your sauce). Toss everything together for ~{2%mins}.

To serve squeeze on 2 tsp of @lime{½} juice and scatter over the @sesame seeds{1} and remaining green parts of the spring onion.